main event: On 23 July 1956, an observer in Hollywood, California reported sighting a light green circular object moving very fast at approximately 20,000 feet altitude.
interesting points: The object was the size of a dime,The object was observed for a length of 3 seconds,The conditions were clear and balmy with good visibility due to a full moon,The object was out of visual sight after the short observation,The conclusion of the report suggests the object was probably astronomical.
witness description: unidentified observer, approximately 59 years old, scanning for aircraft
